  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In the movie \"Avengers: Age of Ultron,\" there's a scene where various Avengers attempt to lift Thor's hammer, Mj\u00f6lnir, which can traditionally only be lifted by someone who is \"worthy.\" When Captain America makes his attempt, the hammer slightly moves or shakes, which indicates that he is potentially worthy but has not fully embraced his worthiness at that moment, or perhaps he holds some internal doubt or humility that prevents him from lifting it completely.\n\nThis scene foreshadows Captain America's true worthiness, which becomes evident in \"Avengers: Endgame,\" where he indeed lifts and wields Mj\u00f6lnir, proving his complete worthiness as it aligns with the values of being honorable, selfless, and pure-hearted.",
